════════════════════════════════════
4. CUSTOM ITEM DIMENSIONS
════════════════════════════════════

Add a custom item form so the user can enter the dimensions of the item they want to place.

Fields:

- Item name
- Width
- Depth
- Height
- Unit selector
- Optional image upload for the item
- Add to room button

Important:
The item crop/measurement frame belongs to the furniture item after it is added to the canvas, not to the room setup.

When a custom item is added, create a furniture object on the canvas with its footprint and height visualization.

════════════════════════════════════
5. FURNITURE PLACEMENT CANVAS
════════════════════════════════════

After the floor is confirmed, the user should be able to add furniture onto the room photo.

Each placed furniture item should have:

- Draggable image
- Rotation handle or rotate buttons
- Scale controls
- Delete button
- Bring forward / send backward optional
- Dimension overlay

For each placed item, show a dedicated item footprint frame:

- Blue dashed rectangle on the floor
- The rectangle represents width x depth
- Dimension labels on the rectangle edges
- Green vertical height indicator next to the item
- Height label beside the green line

Example labels:

Width: 220 cm
Depth: 95 cm
Height: 70 cm

The user should always understand two things:

1. Room dimensions
2. Item dimensions

The room dimensions should stay connected to the gold floor frame.
The item dimensions should stay connected to each placed furniture item.

Do not confuse the two.

Important visual rule:

- Gold frame = room/floor dimensions
- Blue frame = furniture item footprint
- Green line = furniture item height

════════════════════════════════════
6. UNIT HANDLING
════════════════════════════════════

Allow the user to choose preferred units:

- cm
- m
- inches
- feet

All visible labels should update based on the selected unit.

This applies to:

- Room width
- Room depth
- Room height
- Furniture width
- Furniture depth
- Furniture height
- Custom item dimensions

Use simple conversion logic.

════════════════════════════════════
7. UX/UI REQUIREMENTS
════════════════════════════════════

Make the interface very clear and not confusing.

Use clear buttons:

- Upload photo
- Confirm floor
- Adjust floor
- Add furniture
- Add custom item
- Delete item
- Rotate
- Reset

Avoid too many panels at once.

Use a clean layout.

Desktop:

- Canvas large in center
- Furniture/catalog panel on the right
- Step controls at the top

Mobile:

- Canvas on top
- Furniture strip at bottom
- Controls in collapsible panels if needed

Style:

- Modern, clean, minimal
- Gold for room/floor frame
- Blue for item footprint
- Green for height indicator
- White labels with dark background pills for readability
- Clear spacing
- Large enough controls to drag easily
- No clutter

The app should feel like a practical tool, not a marketing website.

════════════════════════════════════
8. IMPORTANT BEHAVIOR
════════════════════════════════════

The floor frame is for the room only.

The blue crop/footprint frame is for furniture items only.

Room dimensions should be entered once after marking the floor.

Furniture dimensions should come from the catalog item or custom item form.

If the user changes the preferred unit, all labels should update.

If no floor is confirmed, allow free placement but hide room dimension labels.

Do not add backend logic.
Do not add Supabase.
Do not add Stripe.
Do not add accounts.
Do not add dashboards.
Do not add AI scene analysis.
Do not add ecommerce.
Do not add product checkout.
Do not add store management.

════════════════════════════════════
9. ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
════════════════════════════════════

The prototype is successful if:

- I can upload a room photo
- I can adjust a document-scanner-style floor frame
- I can enter real room dimensions
- I can see room dimensions on the floor frame
- I can add furniture to the room
- Each furniture item shows its own width, depth, and height
- Each furniture item has its own blue footprint frame
- Height is shown with a green vertical indicator
- I can add a custom item with my own dimensions
- I can choose my preferred unit
- The app feels simple and understandable
- The room frame and item frame are visually different and not confusing

Build this as a fast validation prototype. Prioritize the core interaction over production polish.
